SRC="InstLogoSmall.gif"
WIDTH="198" HEIGHT="57" ALIGN="BOTTOM" NATURALSIZEFLAG="3">
<H3>Mission</H3>
<FONT SIZE="6">T</FONT>he Institute's purpose is to promote the 
opportunities
of persons with disabilities to gain more personal and political power,
self-determination, full participation and equality in Sweden and 
internationally
through educational activities. These activities may consist of the 
production
and dissemination of educational materials and information, planning and
organizing of courses, seminars and study visits.<BR>
<BR>
The Institute is to work in close cooperation with other organizations 
which
support these aims at the local, national and international level 
including
developing countries. The Institute shall cooperate and coordinate its 
activities
with similar centers for research, training and information which promote

self-determination for persons with disabilities. 
<H3>Background</H3>
<FONT SIZE="6">I</FONT>n April 1989 at the European Parliament in 
Strasbourg
over 80 persons with extensive disabilities participated in a 3 day 
conference
on personal assistance. Druing this event <A 
HREF="ENIL/ENILhomepage.html">ENIL</A>,
the European Network on Independent Living was founded.<BR>
<BR>
Two of the Independent Living grassroots organiztions represented at the
Strasbourg meeting, STIL, the Stockholm Cooperative for Independent 
Living,
and GIL, the Gothenburg Independent Living coop, together founded the 
Institute
in 1993 in order to promote the growth of the Indepenent Living movement
within Sweden and internationally through information and educational 
activities.
<H3>Organization</H3>
<FONT SIZE="6">T</FONT>he Institute is a duly registered not-for-profit
foundation according to Swedish law. The following persons serve on the
board 
<BLOCKQUOTE>Rolf Bergfors, GIL, Sweden, <A 
HREF="mailto:rbergfors@mailbox.kdtnet.se">rbergfors@mailbox.kdtnet.se</A>

<BR>
Phillip Mason, United Kingdom, <A 
HREF="mailto:100753.1164@compuserve.com">100753.1164@compuserve.com</A>
<BR>
Adolf Ratzka, STIL, Sweden, chair, <A 
HREF="mailto:ratzka@independentliving.org">ratzka@independentliving.org</
A>
<BR>
Bente Skansg&aring;rd, Norway, <A 
HREF="mailto:Hecter@msn.com">Hecter@msn.com</A></BLOCKQUOTE>
<H3>Consultancy</H3>
<FONT SIZE="6">I</FONT>n the process of building its own website with 
pages
on resources for Independent Living, the Institute has gathered 
experience
in the technical aspects of Internet publishing and can assist other 
organizations
in buidling their websites.<BR>
<BR>
Institute on Independent Living<BR>
<A HREF="Ratzka.html">Adolf D.Ratzka, Ph D, Director</A><BR>
