<HEAD>
    <TITLE>ENILMinutesAGM606.html</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#010336" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" LINK="#00007f">
<BR>
<BR>
<IMG SRC="ENILlogoblues.gif" WIDTH="311" HEIGHT="61" ALIGN="BOTTOM" 
NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><BR>
<BR>
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="1" CELLPADDING="1" WIDTH="100%"> <TR> <TH>

<BR>
<BR>
<B><FONT SIZE="5">Minutes of the</FONT></B><BR>
<BR>
<B><FONT SIZE="5">ENIL </FONT></B><BR>
<BR>
<B><FONT SIZE="5">Assembly General Meeting </FONT></B><BR>
<BR>
<B><FONT SIZE="5">Stockholm </FONT></B><BR>
<BR>
<B><FONT SIZE="5">June 11, 1996</FONT></B> </TH><TD VALIGN="bottom"> <BR>

<BR>
<IMG SRC="../Stadshus.gif" WIDTH="150" HEIGHT="285" X="SAS-UseImageWidth" 
X="SAS-UseImageHeight" ALIGN="RIGHT" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"> </TD></TR> 
</TABLE><BR>
<BR>
<B>Participants</B><BR>
<BR>
The following persons attended:<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Manfred Srb, Austria; Jos Huys, Belgium; Regina Reichert, 
Germany;
Horst Frehe, Germany; Arthur O&acute;Daly, Ireland; Patrizia Moradei, 
Italy;
Bente Skansg&aring;rd, Norway; Knud Flaaum, Norway; Vibeke Melstrom, 
Norway;
Kurt Ahlstr&ouml;m, Sweden; Rolf Bergfors, Sweden; Anki Celander, Sweden;

Adolf Ratzka, Sweden; Lena Stenstr&ouml;m, Sweden; John Evans, UK; Phil
Mason, UK.<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR>
<B>1. Election of officers</B><BR>
The following officers for the meeting were elected by the Assembly<BR>
John Evans, chair; Adolf Ratzka, minute taker; Phil Mason and Horst 
Frehe,
electoral supervisors.<BR>
<BR>
<B>2. Quorum<BR>
</B>The present members fulfilled the conditions of the quorum according
to the new Statutes. There were 16 members from 8 countries.<BR>
<BR>
<B>3. Adoption of the ENIL Statute</B><BR>
The meting discussed, amended and unanimously adopted the draft of the 
Statutes
that had been circulated.<BR>
<BR>
<B>4. &quot;Procedures&quot;</B><BR>
The meeting decided to use the present text of the &quot;<A 
HREF="ENILStockholm96Program.html#anchor930298">Procedures</A>&quot;
as an interim solution and to charge the new Board with the task of 
presenting
the text to the next ENIL Assembly for revision and adoption.<A 
NAME="anchor836316"></A><BR>
<BR>
<B>5. Election of new Board</B><BR>
The meeting decided to elect six (6) Board members at the present meeting

and another three (3) at the next ENIL Assembly. Seven (7) candidates 
were
identified. The following six (6) were elected by simple majority:<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>Manfred Srb, Austria;<BR>
Regina Reichert, Germany;<BR>
Bente Skansg&auml;rd, Norway;<BR>
Adolf Ratzka, Sweden;<BR>
John Evans, UK;<BR>
Gordana Rajkov, Yugoslavia.<BR>
</BLOCKQUOTE>
All votes were valid.<BR>
<BR>
<B>6. Membership of ENIL in the Independent European Disability 
Forum</B><BR>
The Assembly decided unanimously to have ENIL apply for membership as an
NGO in the newly formed Independent European Disability Forum under the
provision that the Forum&acute;s statutes do not violate the purpose of
ENIL as stated in ENIL&acute;s Statutes.<BR>
<BR>
<B>7. Registration as an international NGO in Sweden</B><BR>
The Assembly decided unanimously to have ENIL registered as an 
international
NGO with seat in Sweden.<BR>
<BR>
<B>8. Right to sign application for registration of ENIL</B><BR>
The meeting delegated the right to sign the application for the 
registration
of ENIL as an NGO in Sweden to John Evans and Adolf Ratzka.<BR>
<BR>
<B>9. Membership fees</B><BR>
The meeting decided to charge the Board with the task of preparing a 
membership
fee policy and to present it to the next ENIL Assembly.<BR>
<BR>
<B>10. Electoral Committee</B><BR>
The Assembly elected Phil Mason, Rolf Bergfors and Dinah Radtke to form
the Electoral Committee.<BR>
<BR>
<B>11. Immediate adoption of the minutes</B><BR>
The Assembly decided unanimously to immediately adopt the minutes of the
present Assembly meeting.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="1" WIDTH="80%"> <TR> <TD VALIGN="top"> 
<BR>
<BR>
Signed </TD><TD> <BR>
<BR>
&nbsp; </TD><TD> <BR>
<BR>
Stockholm June 11, 1996 </TD></TR> <TR> <TD> <BR>
<BR>
&nbsp; </TD><TD> <BR>
<BR>
&nbsp; </TD><TD> <BR>
<BR>
&nbsp; </TD></TR> <TR> <TD> <BR>
<BR>
John Evans chair of the meeting </TD><TD> <BR>
<BR>
&nbsp; </TD><TD> <BR>
<BR>
Adolf Ratzka minute taker </TD></TR> </TABLE>
