<HTML>
<TITLE>Psychology Press</TITLE>
<BODY BGCOLOR="FFFFFF" TEXT="000000">
<BR>
<CENTER><IMG BORDER = 1 SRC = "pplgolin.gif" ><BR>
<BR>
<H3>Psychology Press</H3></CENTER>
<BR>
Psychology Press is a new imprint of Erlbaum (UK) Taylor &amp  Francis. From January 1996, all new 
book, journal and multimedia titles published by Erlbaum (UK) will bear the Psychology Press imprint, as 
will reprints of existing publications. Many of these titles were originally published under the imprint 
"Lawrence Erlbaum Associates Ltd". <BR>
<BR>
Psychology Press is an imprint created specifically to serve the needs of researchers, professionals and 
students concerned with the science of human and animal behaviour. It will publish at all levels, including 
primary research journals,  monographs, professional books, student texts and credible scientifically valid 
popular books. <BR>
<BR>
It will publish psychology in its broadest sense, encompassing work of psychological significance by 
people in related areas,  such as biology, neuroscience, linguistics, sociology,  artificial intelligence, as well 
as the work of mainstream psychologists. Its publications will be of interest to any discipline which is 
concerned in any way with the science of human and animal behaviour.<BR>
<BR>
Psychology Press will have a consistent global editorial and marketing policy. Based on the highly 
successful list of Erlbaum (UK) it will eventually integrate and expand the various psychology publishing 
activities within the Taylor and Francis group worldwide, including its offices in London &amp  Hove in 
the UK and Washington and Philadelphia in the USA,  under the direction of Michael Forster and Rohays 
Perry. <BR>
<BR>
We intend that Psychology Press will become the publisher of choice for psychologists worldwide, 
producing and effectively promoting first rate books and journals at competitive prices,  continuing and 
giving a global dimension to the successful tradition of Erlbaum (UK).<BR>
<BR>
<UL>
<LI><A HREF = "mainjnls.htm">Click here</A>    for more information on Psychology Press 
Journals
<LI><A HREF = "mainbks.htm">Click here</A>   for more information on Psychology Press Books
</UL>
<BR>
